Which are the driving factors of the Low-Carb Diet market?

The key drivers of the Low-Carb Diet market include technological advancements that improve product efficiency and user experience, growing consumer demand driven by shifting lifestyle preferences, and supportive government regulations and policies that encourage market growth. Additionally, increased investment in research and development, along with the expanding use of low-carb diets across various industries, further accelerates market expansion.

